Section 1:
1 L.D. 1666
2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 VETERANS AND LEGAL AFFAIRS
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 660, L.D. 1666, “An Act to Include in
10 the Ranked-choice Election Method for General and Special Elections the Offices of
11 Governor, State Senator and State Representative and to Make Other Related Changes”
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in subsection 35-A in the last line (page 1, line 12 in L.D.)
13 by inserting after the following: "elected." the following: 'For the purposes of this
14 subsection, "continuing candidate" has the same meaning as in section 723-A, subsection
15 1, paragraph C and "highest continuing ranking" has the same meaning as in section 723-A,
16 subsection 1, paragraph E.'
17 Amend the bill in section 10 in paragraph I in the 2nd line (page 2, line 31 in L.D.) by
18 inserting after the following: "candidates" the following: 'for that office'
19 Amend the bill in section 10 in paragraph I in the 3rd line (page 2, line 32 in L.D.) by
20 inserting after the following: "ranking" the following: 'of a candidate for an office'
21 Amend the bill in section 10 in paragraph I in the 4th line (page 2, line 33 in L.D.) by
22 inserting after the following: "count" the following: 'in the election for that office'
23 Amend the bill in section 11 in paragraph J in the first line (page 2, line 37 in L.D.) by
24 striking out the following: "ballot counting" and inserting the following: 'counting ballot
25 tabulation'
26 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 12 and inserting the following:
27 'Sec. 12. 21-A MRSA §723-A, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2023, c. 628, §2, is
28 further amended to read:
29 2. Procedures. Except as provided in subsections 3, 4 and 7, the following procedures
30 are used to determine the winner of an election determined by ranked-choice voting. The
31 ranked‑choice voting count ballot tabulation must proceed in rounds. In each round, the
32 number of votes for each continuing candidate must be counted. Each continuing ballot
33 counts as one vote is tabulated for its highest-ranked continuing candidate for that round.
34 Exhausted ballots are not counted tabulated for any continuing candidate. The round then
35 ends with one of the following 2 potential outcomes.
Page 1 - 132LR1668(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 660, L.D. 1666
1 A. If there are 2 or fewer continuing candidates, the ranked-choice voting ballot
2 tabulation is complete and each ballot is tabulated as one vote for its highest-ranked
3 continuing candidate, and the candidate with the most receiving a plurality of the votes
4 cast is declared the winner of the election elected.
5 B. If there are more than 2 continuing candidates, the last-place candidate is removed
6 from consideration eliminated and a new round begins.'
7 Amend the bill in section 13 in subsection 5 in the last line (page 3, line 20 in L.D.) by
8 striking out the following: "counting" and inserting the following: 'tabulation'
9 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
10 number to read consecutively.
11 SUMMARY
1122 This amendment makes technical adjustments to the bill. It includes statutory
1133 references to defined terms used in the definition of "ranked-choice voting." It replaces the
1144 term "count" with the term "tabulate" when referring to the process of determining the
1155 number of votes cast for a candidate in each round of an election determined by
1166 ranked-choice voting. It also clarifies that in the definition of "ranking" the preference
1177 being demonstrated by the voter for a candidate is relative to other candidates for the same
1188 office on that ballot.
Page 2 - 132LR1668(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
